I feel like ghee is such an underrated ingredient. Sure we use it in cooking Indian food but there’s so much more you can do with it. 
Plus I could wax poetic for days about its many benefits …. Skin, gut, bones …..
Trick is to find un adulterated , high quality ghee and for me , that is the @bharatvedicaorganics A2 ghee. 
Here’s my recipe for nutritious, nutty puffed amaranth bars made with a divine , healthy caramel sauce. 

⸻

🍯 Jaggery-Ghee Caramel Bars

Ingredients:
1 cup puffed amaranth 
1/4 cup chopped nuts
2 tbsp mixed seeds
1/2 cup jaggery
2–3 tbsp ghee
2 tbsp water
Pinch of pink salt
Cardamom/vanilla (optional)

Steps:
	1.	Pop and roast the Amaranth, nuts & seeds.
	2.	Melt jaggery + water on low heat till syrupy.
	3.	Add ghee and salt. Still till thickened. 
	4.	Mix in millet-nut blend quickly with a drizzle of vanilla. 
	5.	Spread in a greased tray & press. Cool, cut & enjoy!

✨ Crunchy, sweet, & wholesome!  #HealthySnacks #organic #cookwithmi
